The paper deals with sampling and estimation of statistics on unaggregated data, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus on frequency statistics and the use of cap statistics is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper's emphasis on streaming and distributed data makes it relevant to systems and networking (cs.SI).
